      <p>Social media is simultaneously the most overrated and the most underused lead generation channel. Overrated because most businesses treat it as a broadcast medium — posting content, measuring likes, and wondering why no leads appear. Underused because the platforms that host billions of active users have built increasingly sophisticated tools specifically for capturing and converting leads, and most businesses are barely scratching the surface of what is possible.</p>

      <p>The gap between those two realities is the opportunity this guide addresses. Social media lead generation is not about going viral or building a massive following. It is about using the right mechanics — organic engagement, community positioning, and paid lead capture formats — to move platform users from passive scrollers into identifiable prospects.</p>

      <p>This guide covers five major platforms (Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, TikTok, YouTube) with honest assessments of what each platform produces, who it is relevant for, and what the organic and paid mechanics actually look like in practice. It ends with a platform selection matrix and a stacking framework for combining channels as your volume requirements grow.</p>

