    <section id="section-8">
      <h2>8. Cross-platform lead generation strategy</h2>

      <p>Once a primary platform is producing consistent leads, the natural question is whether to add a second platform. The answer depends on whether the goal is to reach more of the same audience (diversification) or to reach a different audience (expansion).</p>

      <div class="stack-box">
        <h3>The Social Lead Generation Stack — build in sequence</h3>

        <div class="stack-phase">
          <span class="sp-badge">PHASE 1</span>
          <p><strong>Primary platform — organic:</strong> Choose one platform. Build your profile, establish community presence, produce consistent content, and engage actively. Target: first consistent organic lead flow (5–10 leads per week). Timeline: 4–12 weeks depending on effort.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stack-phase">
          <span class="sp-badge">PHASE 2</span>
          <p><strong>Primary platform — paid amplification:</strong> Once organic processes are established, add paid advertising on the same platform. The audience data from organic (which content resonates, what questions come up, what objections appear in comments) informs paid creative. Run Lead Ads targeting a profile similar to your best organic leads. This produces controllable, scalable volume.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stack-phase">
          <span class="sp-badge">PHASE 3</span>
          <p><strong>Email follow-up layer:</strong> Every lead from Phase 1 and 2 should enter an email sequence. Social media leads need follow-up — the lead form capture is the beginning of the relationship, not the sale. A 5–7 email welcome sequence that delivers value and builds trust before a commercial offer is the most reliable conversion mechanism for social media leads.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stack-phase">
          <span class="sp-badge">PHASE 4</span>
          <p><strong>Secondary platform — repurposing first:</strong> Repurpose your highest-performing primary platform content for a second platform rather than creating new content from scratch. A Facebook post that generated significant engagement becomes an Instagram caption. A YouTube video becomes TikTok clips. This extends reach without proportionally increasing production effort.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stack-phase">
          <span class="sp-badge">PHASE 5</span>
          <p><strong>Retargeting across platforms:</strong> Custom Audiences (Facebook/Instagram) and Matched Audiences (LinkedIn) allow you to serve paid ads specifically to people who have already engaged with your content, visited your website, or submitted a previous form. Retargeting campaigns targeting warm audiences consistently produce the lowest cost per lead and highest conversion rates of any paid social tactic.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>For a comparison of how social media fits alongside other lead generation channels (content marketing, email, SEO, paid search), see the full <a href="/blog/lead-generation-strategies/">lead generation strategies playbook</a>. For how social media lead generation applies specifically to local service businesses, see <a href="/blog/local-business-lead-generation/">local business lead generation</a>.</p>
    </section>

