    <section id="faq">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <FaqItem question="What is social media lead generation?" answer="Social media lead generation is the process of using social platforms — Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, TikTok, YouTube — to attract potential customers and capture their contact information or direct purchase intent. It includes organic methods (community participation, content posting, DM conversations) and paid methods (social media advertising, in-platform lead forms). The goal is moving passive platform users into identifiable prospects in your CRM or email list." />

      <FaqItem question="Which social media platform is best for lead generation?" answer="It depends on your audience. Facebook has the broadest demographic reach and the most mature lead capture tools — it is the best starting point for most businesses. LinkedIn is the default for B2B. Instagram works best for visual brands targeting 18–34 audiences. TikTok delivers reach for content-led businesses targeting younger audiences. YouTube is best for high-consideration products and services. The right platform is where your specific buyers already spend time." />

      <FaqItem question="How do you generate leads from social media without paid ads?" answer="Organic social media lead generation uses three tactics: (1) Community participation — joining relevant groups and building visibility through consistent, helpful contributions. (2) Content that captures intent — publishing material that attracts people at the research stage, with a clear call to action directing them to an email opt-in or DM. (3) Direct outreach — identifying prospects through engagement signals and initiating personalised conversations. These produce consistent leads at zero cost beyond time investment, though they scale slowly compared to paid options." />

      <FaqItem question="What are Facebook Lead Ads and how do they work?" answer="Facebook Lead Ads are an ad format that captures contact information within Facebook without sending users to an external page. When clicked, a form opens pre-populated with the user's Facebook profile data. Submission takes two taps. Conversion rates are typically higher than campaigns directing traffic to external landing pages because friction is minimal. Lead data syncs to email platforms via native integrations or Zapier. They work on both Facebook and Instagram through the same campaign setup." />

      <FaqItem question="Is LinkedIn good for lead generation?" answer="LinkedIn is the most effective platform for B2B lead generation. Its audience self-identifies by professional context — job title, industry, company size — allowing targeting precision no other social platform matches for business audiences. Lead quality is consistently high because users are in a professional mindset. Cost per lead is higher than Facebook, but conversion rates and deal values for B2B justify the premium. For consumer businesses, Facebook and Instagram typically deliver better cost efficiency." />

      <FaqItem question="What tools help with social media lead generation?" answer="Key tool categories: (1) Lead capture tools — landing page builders and email opt-ins that receive social traffic (e.g. TD Pages, ConvertKit). (2) Engagement assistance — tools for managing Facebook Group presence at scale (e.g. LeadsMiner Pro, OLSP MineeMe). (3) CRM and follow-up — email marketing platforms that automate sequences for social media leads (e.g. ActiveCampaign, GetResponse). (4) Ad management — native platform tools (Facebook Ads Manager, LinkedIn Campaign Manager) for paid campaigns. For affiliate marketers, the OLSP ecosystem includes purpose-built Facebook lead generation tools." />
    </section>

